http://android-dls.com

https://help.ubuntu.com/community/AndroidScreenshots

In my 10.04LTS, install the openjdk-6-jdk package

Download the Android SDK for Linux. 

wget http://dl.google.com/android/android-sdk_r06-linux_86.tgz

the udev rule:

    peter@peter-laptop:/etc/udev/rules.d$ cat 90-android.rules 
    SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTRS{idVendor}=="22b8", MODE="0666"
    peter@peter-laptop:/etc/udev/rules.d$ 

I get the above idVendor with this:

    peter@peter-laptop:~$ lsusb |grep -i moto|awk  '{print $6}'|awk -F":" '{print $1}'
    22b8


Enabling USB debugging mode on your phone

   1.

      Go to the Settings application, then Applications > Development.
   2.

      Mark the USB Debugging checkbox: 

NOTE: what did fuck me was that I plug usb, then I chose "usb drive", while
infact I should say "charge only"

OK, now connection established.

## adb shell

    peter@peter-laptop:~/Desktop/android-sdk-linux_86/tools$ ./adb shell

done
